      "writtenOn": "2019-05-20T21:44:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I don\u0027t think this is accurate. BT supports column filters to fetch only the columns you want.\nhttps://godoc.org/cloud.google.com/go/bigtable#ColumnFilter\nhttps://godoc.org/cloud.google.com/go/bigtable#ColumnRangeFilter\nhttps://godoc.org/cloud.google.com/go/bigtable#FamilyFilter\n\n(It\u0027s possible that the tablet server will read the entire row from disk, but it won\u0027t return the entire row in the RPC response.)\n\nAssuming a ColumnRangeFilter is reasonably efficient, we could store digests for 11 billion commits in a single row, by my calculations, with the ability to query for any range of commits.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 46,
        "startChar": 51,
        "endLine": 47,
        "endChar": 13
      },
      "revId": "cecf8a2707c82dfaacceb1f212496238f1605937",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
